Next, we deduced the transcription rate, i.e. how frequently each segment of mRNAs (head, body and tail) is synthesized. The law of mass action describes that the change of the mRNA concentration, m, is determined by the balance between the transcription rate, α, and the degradation rate, β, in the following way,
(1)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
\usepackage{amssymb} 
