\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
}{}\begin{equation*}\frac{{dm}}{{dt}} = \alpha - \beta \cdot m\end{equation*}\end{document}
Hence, immediately after induction, when the mRNA level is low (m ≈ 0), we have \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
\usepackage{amssymb} 
