\begin{document}
}{}$\beta \ = \ \alpha /{m_{\rm s}}$\end{document}, where ms refers to the copy number of mRNAs in the steady state. When mRNA expression is fully induced, we observed that ms of the head is ∼6.7 (the value is very similar for the tail). The value, together with α = 5.0/min (as obtained above for the head and also similarly for the tail), yields the degradation rate of 0.75/min. This is less than 2-fold difference from the value obtained using rifampicin above, showing reasonable agreement.
